WEBVTT

00:00.038 --> 00:01.354
<i>Previously, on "Suits..."</i>

00:01.355 --> 00:03.690
There's a whole life
going on here

00:03.725 --> 00:05.525
that you're not even a part of.

00:05.560 --> 00:07.226
You think I don't know
what I've missed?

00:07.262 --> 00:09.395
I'm not just talking about
birthdays, Harvey.

00:09.431 --> 00:10.363
I got sick again.
- What?

00:10.398 --> 00:11.831
Why didn't you tell me?

00:11.866 --> 00:13.299
- Did you know?
- Know what?

00:13.335 --> 00:14.300
That Gavin Andrews
was gonna ask me

00:14.336 --> 00:15.668
to launder money
for him?

00:15.704 --> 00:16.869
Help me get out of this.

00:16.905 --> 00:18.271
Please, Samantha.

00:18.306 --> 00:20.406
I should have listened to you,
but I have a family.

00:20.442 --> 00:22.742
I want to make a perfect baby
with you.

00:22.777 --> 00:24.611
- Are you sure?
- Absolutely.

00:24.646 --> 00:26.579
And I don't want to just be
pulling the goalie.

00:26.615 --> 00:29.382
I want to start trying, and I
want to start trying right now.

00:29.417 --> 00:31.684
I know you think we're in
competition for the same thing,

00:31.720 --> 00:32.819
but we're not.

00:32.854 --> 00:35.221
Robert Zane made me a promise:

00:35.256 --> 00:36.834
the next name that goes up on
the wall is mine.

00:36.858 --> 00:38.424
Why are you telling me this?

00:38.460 --> 00:39.604
Because we're never gonna
trust each other

00:39.628 --> 00:40.638
if you think I'm trying to get
ahead of you.

00:40.662 --> 00:43.084
I'm not, because I already am.

00:47.268 --> 00:48.201
Sheila.

00:48.236 --> 00:49.936
It's after 9:00.
You're gonna be late.

00:49.971 --> 00:51.415
Then I'll be late,
because there's something

00:51.439 --> 00:53.673
I need to ask you.
- Yeah, of course.

00:53.708 --> 00:55.119
- You can ask me anything.
- Louis, have you ever gotten

00:55.143 --> 00:57.143
a woman pregnant before?

00:57.178 --> 00:59.278
Okay, uh...

00:59.314 --> 01:01.347
Where is this going?

01:01.383 --> 01:04.751
I'm asking because
you haven't gotten this woman

01:04.786 --> 01:06.419
pregnant yet either.

01:06.454 --> 01:08.187
Sheila,
we just started trying,

01:08.223 --> 01:09.433
and I think
what I've been doing

01:09.457 --> 01:10.701
is more than meeting
the standards.

01:10.725 --> 01:12.859
Louis, you are
an A/A-plus lover.

01:12.894 --> 01:14.494
Everyone knows that.
- There's a slash?

01:14.529 --> 01:16.129
That's not the point.
The point is,

01:16.164 --> 01:17.930
have you ever considered
the possibility

01:17.966 --> 01:20.466
that you're shooting blanks?
- No more than I would consider

01:20.502 --> 01:21.812
the possibility
that I don't have a face.

01:21.836 --> 01:24.537
I get that, Louis,
and you probably have the sperm

01:24.572 --> 01:27.273
of a thoroughbred,
but I'd like you

01:27.308 --> 01:29.409
to get yourself checked.
- Sheila, if you're asking

01:29.444 --> 01:31.222
what I think you are,
I don't want to go to a place

01:31.246 --> 01:33.312
where people do...

01:33.348 --> 01:34.881
that...

01:34.916 --> 01:36.315
unless it's
absolutely necessary.

01:36.351 --> 01:38.651
I get that, too,
but the fact is,

01:38.687 --> 01:40.564
I'm not getting any younger
and we don't have time

01:40.588 --> 01:43.256
to waste, so I'm getting
myself checked,

01:43.291 --> 01:45.725
and I'm asking you
to do the same.

01:45.760 --> 01:48.428
So here's the address.

01:48.463 --> 01:51.030
You have an appointment today.

01:53.535 --> 01:55.768
Okay, Sheila,
I'll get it done.

01:55.804 --> 01:57.737
Thank you.

01:57.772 --> 01:59.772
Harvey, do you have a second?

01:59.808 --> 02:01.641
- Sure, Louis, what is it?
- Did you ever have

02:01.676 --> 02:03.409
to test your sperm?

02:03.445 --> 02:05.011
- What?
- Sheila wants me to,

02:05.046 --> 02:06.657
but I don't think I can do it
in one of those places.

02:06.681 --> 02:08.425
Louis, I don't want
to have this conversation.

02:08.449 --> 02:09.860
It's bad enough
that we share the same dentist.

02:09.883 --> 02:11.584
Harvey, come on.

02:11.619 --> 02:14.353
We're trying to have a baby,
and I don't have anyone else

02:14.389 --> 02:16.622
to talk to about this.

02:16.658 --> 02:18.591
Okay, what--
what's your problem?

02:18.626 --> 02:22.361
Problem is, I've never had
to do it under duress before.

02:22.397 --> 02:24.530
I don't know how.
- Well, why don't you do it

02:24.566 --> 02:25.932
like everyone else does?

02:25.967 --> 02:27.600
Use pictures.
- I don't use pictures.

02:27.635 --> 02:28.501
I only think of Sheila,
and I can't do that

02:28.536 --> 02:30.002
with a bunch
of strangers there.

02:30.038 --> 02:31.382
Well, what did you do
before Sheila?

02:31.406 --> 02:33.439
- I don't wanna talk about it.
- Well, I don't want

02:33.475 --> 02:34.518
to talk about any of this.
- Harvey, come on.

02:34.542 --> 02:36.776
All right, look...

02:36.811 --> 02:38.644
you can't use pictures;
you don't want

02:38.680 --> 02:40.012
to think about Sheila.

02:40.048 --> 02:41.492
Well, then, you'll have
to think of something

02:41.516 --> 02:42.593
that turns you on
that isn't Sheila.

02:42.617 --> 02:46.319
You mean think about
an inanimate object.

02:46.354 --> 02:48.354
Yes, Louis,
that's what I mean.

02:48.389 --> 02:49.967
- Have you done that before?
- Of course I have.

02:49.991 --> 02:51.469
- What do you use?
- No, I'm not telling you that.

02:51.493 --> 02:53.726
Harvey, please.

02:53.762 --> 02:57.563
All right.
You want the truth?

02:57.599 --> 02:59.665
Sometimes...

02:59.701 --> 03:01.567
I think about...

03:01.603 --> 03:03.369
tomatoes.

03:04.339 --> 03:06.305
- Really?
- Well, if you think about it,

03:06.341 --> 03:08.474
they're the most sensual fruit.
- I thought they were

03:08.510 --> 03:10.076
a vegetable?
- I am opening my soul

03:10.111 --> 03:11.644
to you here;
don't criticize me.

03:11.679 --> 03:13.045
I'm sorry, you're right.

03:13.081 --> 03:16.015
Thank you, Harvey.

03:16.050 --> 03:18.818
Good luck in there, buddy.

03:18.853 --> 03:20.987
Yeah.
Tomatoes, holy shit.

03:21.022 --> 03:23.022
Never thought of that.

03:26.961 --> 03:28.995
You wanna tell me
what that was all about?

03:29.030 --> 03:30.997
No, because I'm guessing
you listened

03:31.032 --> 03:33.833
to the entire conversation,
which means you know

03:33.868 --> 03:35.768
what it's about.
- In that case,

03:35.804 --> 03:37.948
what I really want to know is:
is it true about the tomatoes?

03:37.972 --> 03:39.939
I think we both know
it's not.

03:39.974 --> 03:42.542
Just like we both know
it's really strawberries

03:42.577 --> 03:44.977
and whipped cream.

03:45.013 --> 03:47.413
What, too soon?
- No.

03:47.448 --> 03:49.382
But this is an office,
and someone could overhear

03:49.417 --> 03:51.751
and misunderstand that
that was 13 years ago.

03:51.786 --> 03:53.019
Really?
'Cause it feels like

03:53.054 --> 03:54.554
12 and 1/2 to me.

03:54.589 --> 03:57.056
- You're an idiot.
- No, Louis is an idiot.

03:57.091 --> 04:00.860
because he believed
I think about tomatoes.

04:00.895 --> 04:03.029
And if Sheila wants him
to get his swimmers checked,

04:03.064 --> 04:05.364
we shouldn't mock
that he has to do that...

04:05.400 --> 04:07.033
in a cup...

04:07.068 --> 04:09.602
thinking about tomatoes.
- You're absolutely right.

04:09.637 --> 04:11.137
We should take it
very seriously.

04:11.172 --> 04:13.639
Tomatoes.
- Okay, you know what?

04:13.675 --> 04:15.875
As much as I would love
to do this all day,

04:15.910 --> 04:19.579
I came in here to tell you
you need to call Marcus.

04:19.613 --> 04:20.913
Marcus?
About what?

04:20.949 --> 04:22.882
I don't know,
but he left me a message

04:22.917 --> 04:24.662
that he wants you to call him.
- Well, if he wants me to call,

04:24.686 --> 04:26.619
why would he be leaving
a message for you?

04:26.654 --> 04:29.555
Because when Marcus
really needs you, he calls me.

04:29.591 --> 04:31.490
He's only ever done that twice,

04:31.526 --> 04:34.727
which means whatever it is
he needs, it's important.

04:36.497 --> 04:39.031
All right, Donna,
I'll call him.

04:39.067 --> 04:41.467
Today, Harvey.

04:41.502 --> 04:42.802
Today.

04:50.945 --> 04:52.178
Hey, Harvey.

04:52.213 --> 04:53.946
I'm glad you called.

04:53.982 --> 04:55.092
I take it Donna
gave you my message?

04:55.116 --> 04:57.516
She did.
What's going on?

04:57.552 --> 04:59.685
<i>- I'm getting a divorce.</i>
- What?

04:59.721 --> 05:00.887
<i>I know.</i>

05:00.922 --> 05:03.522
And I know it is a big ask,

05:03.558 --> 05:05.625
but I was hoping
that you could represent me.

05:05.660 --> 05:07.760
Marcus, hold on.
When did this happen?

05:07.795 --> 05:09.540
The last time I was up there
everything seemed fine.

05:09.564 --> 05:11.797
Yeah, well, it's not fine,
and as much as I hate it,

05:11.833 --> 05:13.966
this is what she wants.
- If you want me to help you,

05:14.002 --> 05:15.768
I'm gonna need
to know more than that.

05:15.803 --> 05:16.535
<i>What do you want me</i>
<i>to tell you, Harvey?</i>

05:16.571 --> 05:18.504
<i>That we grew apart?</i>

05:18.539 --> 05:19.783
Well, we did.
<i>- Bullshit, I know you.</i>

05:19.807 --> 05:22.775
It's not the full story.
<i>- You're right, it's not,</i>

05:22.810 --> 05:24.655
and I will tell you everything
when you get up here.

05:24.679 --> 05:26.112
<i>I didn't say</i>
<i>I was coming up there,</i>

05:26.147 --> 05:27.625
and I'm not going to
unless you tell me

05:27.649 --> 05:28.915
what's going on, right now.

05:33.021 --> 05:35.121
I slept with someone,
all right?

05:35.156 --> 05:37.156
- You did what?
<i>- I was stupid,</i>

05:37.191 --> 05:39.125
and I had an affair,
and I know you want

05:39.160 --> 05:41.661
to rip my head off right now--
<i>- You're damn right, I do!</i>

05:41.696 --> 05:43.696
'Cause you know better
than anyone

05:43.731 --> 05:46.232
what that does to a family.
- Right now, I don't care.

05:46.267 --> 05:47.578
What the hell
did you just say to me?

05:47.602 --> 05:49.635
<i>Harvey, you're always</i>
<i>telling your clients</i>

05:49.671 --> 05:51.637
that your issues
are your issues

05:51.673 --> 05:53.550
and that you don't judge people
for what they do.

05:53.574 --> 05:55.975
<i>So right now I don't need</i>
<i>to hear how I screwed up.</i>

05:56.010 --> 05:57.988
What I need to hear is that
you're on your way up here

05:58.012 --> 06:00.146
to help make sure
that I don't lose my kids.

06:00.181 --> 06:01.714
What are you talking about?

06:01.749 --> 06:03.816
I'm talking about custody,
Harvey,

06:03.851 --> 06:06.085
<i>because Katie hired a shark</i>
<i>to represent her.</i>

06:06.120 --> 06:07.887
Which means even if
you didn't want this

06:07.922 --> 06:09.655
to turn into a fight...
<i>- I can't risk</i>

06:09.691 --> 06:11.657
not treating it like one,
and the best way I know

06:11.693 --> 06:13.537
to avoid a fight is to show up
with a howitzer--

06:13.561 --> 06:15.094
and, Harvey...

06:15.129 --> 06:18.698
the biggest howitzer I know
is you.

06:18.733 --> 06:20.166
All right, Marcus,
I'll come up.

